{"MONOECIA":[{"def":"A Linnæan class of plants, whose stamens and pistils are in distinct flowers in the same plant.","pos":""}],"MONOECIAN":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to the Monoecia; monoecious.","pos":""},{"def":"One of the Monoecia.","pos":""}],"MONOECIOUS":[{"def":"Having the sexes united in one individual, as when male and female flowers grow upon the same individual plant; hermaphrodite; -- opposed to Ant: dioecious.","pos":""}],"MONOECISM":[{"def":"The state or condition of being monoecious.","pos":""}]}